# Runtime Reports Module
#
# Reports for runtime events: panics, debug logging, and memory diagnostics.
# Provides structured runtime diagnostics with stack traces and context.
#
# # Quick Start
#
# ```simple
# import std.report.runtime
#
# # Panic handling
# val panic = PanicReport.assertion("expected x > 0")
#     .at("main.spl", 42, 5)
#     .with_stack_trace(trace)
#     .with_context("x", "-5")
#
# # Debug logging
# val logger = Logger.named("my_module")
# logger.debug("Processing item")
# logger.info("Completed successfully")
#
# # Memory diagnostics
# val report = MemoryReport.empty()
# report.add_leak(LeakInfo.at_address(0x1234, 1024))
# ```
#
# # Panic Types
#
# | Kind | Code | Description |
# |------|------|-------------|
# | Assertion | P0001 | Assertion failed |
# | Unreachable | P0002 | Unreachable code reached |
# | IndexOutOfBounds | P0003 | Array index out of bounds |
# | NullPointer | P0004 | Null pointer dereference |
# | DivisionByZero | P0005 | Division by zero |
# | Overflow | P0006 | Integer overflow |
# | StackOverflow | P0007 | Stack overflow |
# | OutOfMemory | P0008 | Memory allocation failed |
#
# # Log Levels
#
# | Level | Use Case |
# |-------|----------|
# | Debug | Detailed diagnostic info |
# | Info | Normal operation events |
# | Warning | Potential issues |
# | Error | Recoverable errors |
#
# # Memory Events
#
# | Event | Description |
# |-------|-------------|
# | Allocation | Memory allocated |
# | Deallocation | Memory freed |
# | GCStart/End | GC cycle |
# | LeakDetected | Memory leak found |

